Such was the  the  was a man,
Whom Nature built on quite a diff'rent plan;
A  whom from the moment he was born,
His Dam despis'd, and left  in scorn;
A  which, the pow'r of Art outdone,
She could not finish when She had begun;
An utter  out of which no might
But that of God could strike one spark of light.
